<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-20T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-20T12:00:00-05:00" n="560" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (<persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName>)/6–2045: Telegram</note>
                                <head>No. 560<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in <persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName>
                                    </hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KMGNJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                        the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                        <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                                    </seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caserta</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-20T19:00:00+02:00">June 20, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                                    </dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>2695. Our 2693, June 20.<note n="1" xml:id="d560fn1">Not
                                        printed.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>Gen <persName corresp="#p_MLGWD1">Morgan</persName> just
                                    telephoned from Monf aleone that agreement<note n="2" xml:id="d560fn2">For the text (in English and
                                        Serbo-Croatian) of the “Agreement Between the Supreme Allied
                                        Commander, Mediterranean Theatre of Operations, and the
                                        Supreme Commander of the Yugoslav Army” signed at Duino on
                                        June 20, 1945, and of appendices C–J thereto, see
                                        Meђyнapoдни Уговори Фeдeративне Нapoдне Рeпyблиĸе
                                        Jугослaвнje, 1945, No. 3 (Belgrade, Ministry of Foreign
                                        Affairs, no date). The maps which comprise appendices A and
                                        B to this agreement are not printed. For the “Note on Civil
                                        Administration of Zone of Venezia Giulia Coming Under Allied
                                        Military Government” signed at the same time, see <ref target="#d561">document No. 561</ref>.</note> with Yugos
                                    was signed at 9 o’clock this morning.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <persName corresp="#p_KMGNJ1">
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                                        </persName>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>